## Section 5 — Common operations

```bash
# Validate the JTBD bundle.
flowforge jtbd lint --bundle workflows/jtbd_bundle.json

# Validate every workflow definition.
flowforge validate --root workflows

# Simulate one JTBD by firing events in order.
flowforge simulate --def workflows/{{ jtbds[0].id if jtbds else "<jtbd>" }}/definition.json --events submit

# Regenerate this file after editing the bundle.
flowforge generate-llmtxt --bundle workflows/jtbd_bundle.json --out llm.txt
```

## Section 6 — Where to look first

- **Edit a JTBD**: `workflows/jtbd_bundle.json` — re-run lint after every save.
- **Edit a workflow definition**: `workflows/<jtbd_id>/definition.json`.
- **Wire a new port** (audit / outbox / rbac / …): `backend/src/{{ project.package }}/workflow_adapter.py`.
- **Add an HTTP handler**: `backend/src/{{ project.package }}/main.py`.
- **Framework-level reference**: use the Flowforge source checkout's `README.md`,
  `docs/jtbd-user-guide.md`, and root `llm.txt` when available.
